External APIs Used:
1. Open-Meteo API (https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast)
Function: Provides free weather forecasting data including temperature, humidity, precipitation, and weather codes.
Usage:
Fetches current weather and 7-day forecasts for farming locations.
Generates weather-based farming recommendations and advisories.
Endpoints Used:
/v1/forecast (used in both weather.js route and farmingLogic.js utility)
2. data.gov.in API (https://api.data.gov.in/resource/)
Function: Official Indian government portal providing real-time agricultural market data.
Usage: Fetches live mandi (market) prices for crops like rice, wheat, corn, etc., from various districts.
Endpoints Used:
Resource ID 9ef273e5-7f2d-4551-86a0-621cae48395f for daily mandi prices
Authentication: Requires API key from data.gov.in
3. whapi.cloud API (https://gate.whapi.cloud/messages/text)
Function: WhatsApp Business API for sending automated messages.
Usage: Sends farming alerts and notifications via WhatsApp.
Authentication: Bearer token required
4. Nominatim API (https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org/reverse)
Function: OpenStreetMap's geocoding service for reverse geocoding.
Usage: Converts latitude/longitude coordinates to human-readable location names (city, town, village).
Headers: Includes User-Agent for identification
5. Twilio API (via twilio npm package)
Function: Cloud communications platform for SMS and WhatsApp messaging.
Usage: Sends farming alerts via SMS and WhatsApp as backup/alternative to whapi.cloud.
Authentication: Account SID and Auth Token required
Additional Notes:
All APIs have fallback mechanisms (mock data) when API keys are missing or services are unavailable.
The project prioritizes Indian government and free/open-source APIs where possible.
Weather and market data are cached/processed locally for better performance.
Authentication keys are stored in environment variables (.env file).
